	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Actually, the standard Arkanoid controller uses an [inverted] NINE-bit data signal where the minimum is 196 and the maximum is 484; evidently, the original used an oscillator (based on the resistance in the varister) and also relied on exactly 1/60th of a second between each strobe to get proper values.

		

		</td>
